features: 📏 Choose the Perfect Fit: Our dish drying rack comes in a range of sizes, ensuring a seamless fit for any kitchen and countertop. With dimensions of 17 x 10 inches, it's specifically designed to complement sinks with a short side of up to 16 inches. Choose the appropriate dimension to effortlessly blend this essential kitchen accessory into your unique kitchen layout.

🔥Non-Slip, FDA-Grade Silicone Materials: Say goodbye to clunky stainless steel racks! Our dish drainer has better convenience and strength and won't squeak, thanks to its non-slip silicone coating. BPA-free and food-safe, it's perfect for fruits, veggies, cakes, etc; It also protects your utensils from scratch.

🔥 Multi-Purpose and Heat-Resistant: The integrated drain board features raised ridges, elevating items from the countertop. With a heat resistance of up to 400°F (204°C), it's your kitchen's guardian against hot items from the oven, stove, or microwave, protecting your countertop from damage.

🚀 Smart Space-Saving Design and Dishwasher Safe: Keep your kitchen organized and clutter-free. Our dish drainer easily collapses for hassle-free storage when not in use! Cleansing is a breeze too - easy wipe clean it or toss it into dishwasher!
💪 Built to Last: Built with sturdy materials, our drainer can hold up to 100 pounds. Unlike fragile, hollow steel racks, it won't warp or break under regular use, ensuring years of reliable service.
💪 Our Promise to You: We stand behind our SAOSHYPEI product's quality with a lifetime warranty. If you have any concerns or questions, our dedicated customer support team is just a message away.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Make sure the width fits your sink and you're good to go.This is great for using your second sink as a drying rack or rinsing station (I wash in one sink, put the clean soapy items in the other sink, and then rinse a bunch at once - but sometimes the second sink is nasty so this is a great option).The silicone is nice and it rolls up nicely for storage under the sink. It's been through a camping trip already (used it on a flat plastic table to dry pots/pans) and it held up to my sister's teenagers.
